UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'AI notes: ### Action Items ### Founders'' Backgrounds - **Gurashish** is from Chandigarh studying at IIT Madras, developed passion for aerospace through NCC Air Force training where they first piloted a plane in 10th class - **Zaid** is from Hyderabad, runs a cooking YouTube channel with 200k subscribers that started during lockdown ### Zenova''s Product & Technology ### Competitive Landscape & Differentiation ### Go-to-Market Strategy Shift ### Current Customer Engagements - **Delhi Airport**: In discussions through GMI Group''s startup program to understand current detection gaps and explore pilot deployment - **Saudi Arabia**: In talks for pilot program, positioning as cost-effective alternative to $2-5M US/European systems ### Fundraising ### Investor Concerns Raised - **Procurement challenges**: 12-18 month sales cycles per customer, painful systems integration work - **Pricing risk**: Concern founders will accept low-ball offers (e.g. $60k/year) without understanding value-based pricing, limiting to 20-30 airport customers - **Product vs services**: Risk of becoming services shop doing custom integration rather than building scalable product platform, which eliminates enterprise value - **Market positioning**: Most large venture investors have already backed competing systems integrators, making fundraising difficult - **Defense quality**: Even if successful in defense, it''s a poor business with 270-day net working capital cycles, buyer concentration risk, and limited expo...' WHERE id = 525 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Meeting Prep — 2026-03-04: ## Conversation Prep Research — Xook.ai ### Auto-generated on 2026-03-04 14:35 IST ## Founders & Background _No founder profiles found in Network DB. Check page content below._ ## Company Synopsis Source: Arjun Rao, GP at Speciale Incept Advisors, forwarded to Rahul. Arjun''s take: "Robotics for Commercial Cafes/Kiosks in the US, founder seems to be on the cusp of something breaking out. Sector and geo isn''t for us." FOUNDER: Rajagopal (Raja) Natarajan WHAT THEY DO: Autonomous robotic kiosks that make and serve fresh food (180+ bowls/hour) in a 60 sqft footprint - "packing output of 1,500 sqft kitchen into a parking space." THE PIVOT: Shifting from low-traffic 24/7 sites to high-volume use cases + on-demand delivery. New kiosk built specifically for lunch/dinner rush "that breaks most other robots." TRACTION: ## Market Map ### Web Research: - Indian AI Startup Tracker: Meet 170+ Startups Putting India On The Global AI Map It is backed by investors like Z47 and Elevation Capital. It counts <strong>Imaginario AI, VideoDubber, and Rephrase AI</strong> as its competitors https://inc42.com/startups/indian-ai-startup-tracker/ - Rajagopal (Raja) Natarajan - Xook | LinkedIn And the ones who make it big in India don’t do it by building more, raising more, and spending more. They do it by building less, with less. When everyone else is racing to integrate the newest tech, https://www.linkedin.com/in/rajagopaln/ - Xook - 2025 Company Profile, Team, Funding, Com...' WHERE id = 526 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'AI notes: This meeting was a customer interview conducted by Prateek from DVC (Matrix Partners India''s early stage investment team) with Rahul from a voice AI company called Bolna. The purpose was to understand Bolna''s experience with XPay, a payment gateway, as part of DVC''s investment evaluation process. Company Background: - Bolna is a voice AI infrastructure company that went viral on GitHub and Twitter - Founded in India but focused on global markets (US, UK, Australia) - Funded by Upekkha, a SaaS accelerator - Recently pivoted to voice AI for the recruitment industry, primarily serving US-based recruitment agencies - Transformed from an Indian Pvt Ltd company to a Delaware C Corp around October 2024 XPay Usage Journey: - Initially couldn''t use Stripe as they were an India-based company - Discovered XPay (YC-backed) when looking for alternatives to accept international payments - Integrated XPay APIs for regular payments - Used XPay custom links for larger clients ($5K-$10K range) - XPay provided automated monthly transaction sheets Reasons for Switching to Stripe: - Needed subscription functionality which XPay didn''t support at the time - Stripe offered better webhook support, error management, and fallback mechanisms - No commission or platform fees with Stripe due to Upekkha''s partnership - Company structure changed to Delaware C Corp, enabling direct Stripe access Current Payment Setup: - Two revenue streams: - Self-serve "pay as you go" where customers top up wallet...' WHERE id = 527 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'Notes:: Founder Backgrounds 1. Siva Kiran (Co-founder): - Education: Graduated from IIT Bombay in 2018. - Career Journey: - Worked for Startup Call and ITI for about 6 years, mostly in the CEO''s office, handling product development, operations efficiency, and special projects. - Worked closely with Amazon on last-mile programs, Amazon Pay, and Video KYC platform (powered by Idify). - Had experience working in Middle East, launching platforms for Amazon and working in Lenskart on special projects. - Also worked with BCG on cost optimization projects across various industries, especially industrial goods and energy. 1. Vishwanadh R. (Co-founder): - Education: Graduated in Computer Science from IIT Kanpur in 2017. - Career Journey: - Started with Microsoft through a PPO (Pre-Placement Offer) after an internship. - Worked as a Quant Trader at Mathesis Advisors, a high-frequency trading firm, for 15 months. - Later, worked at Google for 9 months focusing on Android apps and Nest Home Devices. - Worked at Facebook in London for 2.5 years on building Workplace—Facebook''s enterprise product. - Returned to India to explore the startup ecosystem, looking into sectors like marketing tech, legal tech, AI agents, and ultimately moving toward climate change technologies after reading about global climate disasters and potential solutions. Autobot Energy Overview - Company Mission: - Autobot Energy focuses on providing clean, cheap, and consistent energy through renewable energy sources, ai...' WHERE id = 590 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
UPDATE companies SET agent_ids_notes = 'October ‘25 Investor Update: Quick update as we head into the remaining quarter of the year. We’ve sharpened our positioning and expanded our customer base, working with publicly traded companies — all while zeroing on becoming the best mobile QA solution out there. Below you’ll find recent progress since YC, learnings, our goals, and our asks :) Progress since YC: - In August we had ~$130K ARR, that is now ~$250K ARR with ~$2-2.5M in the pipeline. Working with teams like Fetch Rewards, YC mobile team, [solidcore], and Scribd and many more. - We''ve been doing a POC with DoorDash (~1 month in), which we hope to turn into a pilot ($15-20K/month), which when converted to a complete contract will have an ACV of $500K - $1M (estimate). - In the process of setting up pilots with AAA, 23andMe, Autonation and potentially Pinterest and Rocket Money. Each of these would be $250K-1M in ACV. Exploring if we would fit in heavily as an enterprise solution and maybe switching focus to that. Keeping growth momentum on both ends in the meantime. - Released an experimental caching feature, boosting agent speed by 5-8x per action (tap, swipe, enter text, etc.). - Brought on another engineer who we hope to join us full-time in December (extremely talented, amazing person, & wrapping up his last semester of college). Our team is now at 4 people (2 founders, 1 founding engineer, 1 part-time engineer)! - Cranking on growth: outbound, linkedin presence, case studies, GEO, podcasts, getting creative ...' WHERE id = 592 AND (agent_ids_notes IS NULL OR agent_ids_notes = '');
